# cmd.exe requires CRLF in batch files. With LF-only endings it seeks by byte
# offset through the file and resumes mid-line, running fragments of words as
# if they were commands -- which is exactly what the v1.0.3 release zip did.
#
# This matters for `git archive` as much as for checkout: the in-app updater
# downloads the tag's zip, so whatever ends up in there is what people run.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf

# Everything else: normalise in the repository, leave the working copy alone.
* text=auto
*.png binary
*.onnx binary
*.qm binary
*.seb binary
